byline.contributor: Patricia Torres reported from Caracas, and William Neuman from Máncora, Peru.
byline.original: By PATRICIA TORRES and WILLIAM NEUMAN

abstract: Government of Pres Nicolas Maduro names 13 new judges to Venezuelan Supreme Court, days before swearing-in of newly elected National Assembly which is dominated by political opposition.
lead_paragraph: The legislature, dominated by President Nicolás Maduro’s party, voted in what critics called an attempt to stack the Supreme Court in the executive branch’s favor before an opposition-dominated Assembly took over.

headline.main: Venezuela’s Departing Legislature Approves 13 New Justices

snippet: The legislature, dominated by President Nicolás Maduro’s party, voted in what critics called an attempt to stack the Supreme Court in the executive branch’s favor before an opposition-dominated Assembly took over.
